Let $C_1$ and $C_2$ be circles defined by $(x-10)^2 + y^2 = 36$ and $(x+15)^2 + y^2 = 81$ respectively. What is the length of the shortest line segment $PQ$ that is tangent to $C_1$ at $P$ and to $C_2$ at $Q$? ||| Circle $C_1$ has center $(10,0)$ and radius 6.  Let $A = (10,0).$  Circle $C_2$ has center $(-15,0)$ and radius 9.  Let $B = (-15,0).$

